java.io.Serializable, JboMessage, MetaObjectBase, ExprWrappable, Properties
public class RowFinderFetchLimitExceededException
extends JboException

When a RowFinder executes and finds the number of matching rows is more than expected maximum(maxRows), this Exception is thrown when user specified ErrorIfMaxRowsExceeded to true.

RowFinderFetchLimitExceededException

public RowFinderFetchLimitExceededException(java.lang.String finderName,
                                            java.lang.String rsName)
Creates an exception to be localized using CSMessageBundle and error code EXC_TOO_MANY_ROWS_FOUND.

Parameters:
finderName - the name of finder which returns more rows than maximum number.
rsName - the name of row set the finder execute on.
